{"word":"κλονέω","slug":"κλονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλονέω</b></el> <el>(κλονέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κλόνος'><el>κλόνος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to drive in confusion, drive before one</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>to ruffle</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be driven in confusion, rush wildly</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be beaten by the waves</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}